- Earlier package review found pycache/pyc residue in one zip. Make sure final package removes it.

Current concern:
Do not rely on claims. Verify artifacts directly.
If someone says a dataset was processed, require receipts:
- dataset name
- raw source path
- raw file count
- raw total bytes
- staged path
- staged file count
- staged total bytes
- counts path
- counts bytes before/after
- counts modified time before/after
- lexicon bytes before/after
- coordinate index path and row count
- citation path and row count
- relation observation count
- phase start/end timestamps
- exact command run
- cached artifacts reused or not
- full dataset vs sample/smoke

Classification labels:
- FULL_RUN_CONFIRMED
- CACHE_REUSED
- SAMPLE_ONLY
- METADATA_ONLY
- FAILED_OR_INCOMPLETE
- NOT_RUN
- UNKNOWN

UI direction:
There is an old Clearbox Lexicon UI with useful visual shape, but old backend/business logic must not come forward.
Use only HTML/CSS/layout/theme ideas.
No old Clearbox stores.
No old lexicon/count logic.
No chat memory bridge.
No model calls.
No backend business logic in HTML/CSS/frontend JS.

Desired AWRAG UI concept:
Page 1: Chat + Intake
- dataset/runtime selector
- intake status
- count backend status
- symbol system status
- query/chat box
- evidence packet output
- citation cards
- coordinate cards

Page 2: Evidence Review
- read-only dataset manifest
- dataset-local lexicon search
- anchor detail
- evidence occurrences
- citation lookup
- coordinate lookup
- miss diagnosis

Important UI law:
After intake, admitted data is evidence.
The UI reviews and interrogates evidence.
It does not silently edit evidence.
If data is wrong, request re-ingest or correction receipt.

Bridge rules:
Frontend displays.
Backend bridge translates.
AWRAG decides.

Allowed bridge:
- small backend bridge may call existing AWRAG CLI/API
- may assemble read-only UI views
- may validate UI requests
- may create explicit action receipts

Not allowed:
- count/ranking logic in bridge
- citation authority in bridge
- symbol assignment in bridge
- model prompting in bridge
- old Clearbox business logic in bridge
- raw file editing from UI

Immediate correct workflow:
1. Verify current repo state.
2. Verify native .awbin backend is active.
3. Verify no SQLite hot path.
4. Verify USB/package cleanliness.
5. Only then continue UI or dataset processing.
6. Do not add features until release gate passes.

Release gate must check:
- no __pycache__
- no .pyc
- no sqlite3 runtime import
- no dataset_counts.sqlite
- no hardcoded local paths
- tests pass
- CLI help works
- sample init/intake/status/query works
- .awbin files created
- status reports awrag_native_binary_counts@1
- symbol system reports awrag_public_6b@1
- persistent_memory=false
- outputs watermarked

If asked to work now:
Report first. Do not patch unless explicitly told.
```

Short version for the new Codex:

```text
AWRAG is not a generic RAG toy. It is the public demo slice of the AnchorWorks evidence/count architecture. SQLite was accidentally introduced and is forbidden. Public AWRAG must use demo-safe native .awbin counts with 6-byte public symbols. Dataset data stays dataset-local. No lifetime memory. No model authority. Verify artifacts, do not trust claims.
```

